{
  "stem": "4967.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And nothing remained from the small ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "They dismantled the bridge, and it became only the one ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] And life carried on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And people tried to avoid to go to the doctors in the big ghetto, because they-- they never knew if the hospital will be blown up again or whatever will happen.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we suffered bitter frost in 1943.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It was very cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "As I said previously, we dismantled any firewood, whatever possible was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the trouble started when the Germans find out that the Jewish people in the ghetto got infected with lice and other insects, parasites.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "So they build it, this disinfectant [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] unit, which consists-- consisted of hot showers, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] steamed the clothing by the wall, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and-- but not gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We didn't know about gas chambers in those days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And every two weeks, we had to go to have a shower and de-lice our clothing that we used to wear.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And I think typhoid broke out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But some disease broke out in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But we were able to handle it under control.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "People used to die from starvation, from disease, and from beating out from nowhere.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "If you walk in the streets or-- or to go to work, the Germans would just kick you or beat you up with their batons or with their rifles.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it was dangerous even to go to work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "The people who worked on the airfields, on the airport for the Germans, used to be beaten up to death.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "They had to march to work and back from work.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
